{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775841005846,"sessionID":"ses_287a0d953ffeprum1kjA3lYblB","part":{"id":"prt_d785f4cb7001uKC2W6YTei6JJg","messageID":"msg_d785f456a001G5HWGctPntsdO1","sessionID":"ses_287a0d953ffeprum1kjA3lYblB","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-e19f89a053e340a6bcb410fba1916a90","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: package v1alpha1\n2: \n3: import (\n4: \tmetav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n5: \t\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/util/intstr\"\n6: )\n7: \n8: // +genclient\n9: // +genclient:nonNamespaced\n10: // +k8s:deepcopy-gen:interfaces=k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object\n11: // +k8s:openapi-gen=true\n12: // +kubebuilder:resource:shortName=ar;agentruntime\n13: // +kubebuilder:subresource:status\n14: // +kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"Age\",type=\"date\",JSONPath=\".metadata.creationTimestamp\"\n15: \n16: // AgentRuntime defines a custom resource for managing agent runtime configurations.\n17: // It represents a sandbox orchestration runtime that manages the lifecycle of agent pods.\n18: type AgentRuntime struct {\n19: \tmetav1.TypeMeta   `json:\",inline\"`\n20: \tmetav1.ObjectMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n21: \n22: \tSpec   AgentRuntimeSpec   `json:\"spec,omitempty\"`\n23: \tStatus AgentRuntimeStatus `json:\"status,omitempty\"`\n24: }\n25: \n26: // AgentRuntimeSpec defines the desired state of an AgentRuntime.\n27: type AgentRuntimeSpec struct {\n28: \t// PodTemplate defines the template for creating sandbox pods.\n29: \t// +required\n30: \tPodTemplate *SandboxTemplate `json:\"podTemplate\"`\n31: \n32: \t// SessionTimeout defines the timeout for idle sessions before cleanup.\n33: \t// +kubebuilder:default=\"15m\"\n34: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Type=string\n35: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Format=duration\n36: \t// +optional\n37: \tSessionTimeout *metav1.Duration `json:\"sessionTimeout,omitempty\"`\n38: \n39: \t// MaxSessionDuration defines the maximum allowed duration for a session.\n40: \t// +kubebuilder:default=\"8h\"\n41: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Type=string\n42: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Format=duration\n43: \t// +optional\n44: \tMaxSessionDuration *metav1.Duration `json:\"maxSessionDuration,omitempty\"`\n45: }\n46: \n47: // SandboxTemplate defines the template for creating sandbox pods.\n48: type SandboxTemplate struct {\n49: \t// Metadata defines labels and annotations for the pod.\n50: \t// +optional\n51: \tMetadata *SandboxMetadata `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n52: \n53: \t// Spec defines the pod specification.\n54: \tSpec SandboxPodSpec `json:\"spec\"`\n55: }\n56: \n57: // SandboxMetadata defines metadata for sandbox pods.\n58: type SandboxMetadata struct {\n59: \t// Labels are key-value pairs attached to the pod.\n60: \t// +optional\n61: \tLabels map[string]string `json:\"labels,omitempty\"`\n62: \n63: \t// Annotations are unstructured key-value pairs stored with the pod.\n64: \t// +optional\n65: \tAnnotations map[string]string `json:\"annotations,omitempty\"`\n66: }\n67: \n68: // SandboxPodSpec defines the specification for sandbox pods.\n69: type SandboxPodSpec struct {\n70: \t// Containers represents the list of containers in the pod.\n71: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:MinItems=1\n72: \tContainers []SandboxContainer `json:\"containers\"`\n73: \n74: \t// NodeSelector specifies node selection constraints.\n75: \t// +optional\n76: \tNodeSelector map[string]string `json:\"nodeSelector,omitempty\"`\n77: \n78: \t// Affinity defines pod scheduling constraints.\n79: \t// +optional\n80: \tAffinity *SandboxAffinity `json:\"affinity,omitempty\"`\n81: \n82: \t// Tolerations defines pod tolerations.\n83: \t// +optional\n84: \tTolerations []SandboxToleration `json:\"tolerations,omitempty\"`\n85: \n86: \t// ResourceRequirements defines resource requirements for the pod.\n87: \t// +optional\n88: \tResourceRequirements *SandboxResources `json:\"resources,omitempty\"`\n89: \n90: \t// Volumes defines pod volumes.\n91: \t// +optional\n92: \tVolumes []SandboxVolume `json:\"volumes,omitempty\"`\n93: }\n94: \n95: // SandboxContainer defines a container in a sandbox pod.\n96: type SandboxContainer struct {\n97: \t// Name is the name of the container.\n98: \t// +required\n99: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:MinLength=1\n100: \tName string `json:\"name\"`\n101: \n102: \t// Image is the container image.\n103: \t// +required\n104: \tImage string `json:\"image\"`\n105: \n106: \t// Command specifies the entrypoint array for the container.\n107: \t// +optional\n108: \tCommand []string `json:\"command,omitempty\"`\n109: \n110: \t// Args specifies the arguments to the entrypoint.\n111: \t// +optional\n112: \tArgs []string `json:\"args,omitempty\"`\n113: \n114: \t// WorkingDir specifies the working directory.\n115: \t// +optional\n116: \tWorkingDir string `json:\"workingDir,omitempty\"`\n117: \n118: \t// Ports represents the network ports exposed by the container.\n119: \t// +optional\n120: \tPorts []SandboxContainerPort `json:\"ports,omitempty\"`\n121: \n122: \t// Env represents environment variables.\n123: \t// +optional\n124: \tEnv []SandboxEnvVar `json:\"env,omitempty\"`\n125: \n126: \t// Resources defines compute resource requirements.\n127: \t// +optional\n128: \tResources *SandboxContainerResources `json:\"resources,omitempty\"`\n129: \n130: \t// VolumeMounts specifies volume mounts.\n131: \t// +optional\n132: \tVolumeMounts []SandboxVolumeMount `json:\"volumeMounts,omitempty\"`\n133: \n134: \t// LivenessProbe defines the liveness probe.\n135: \t// +optional\n136: \tLivenessProbe *SandboxProbe `json:\"livenessProbe,omitempty\"`\n137: \n138: \t// ReadinessProbe defines the readiness probe.\n139: \t// +optional\n140: \tReadinessProbe *SandboxProbe `json:\"readinessProbe,omitempty\"`\n141: \n142: \t// SecurityContext defines security settings.\n143: \t// +optional\n144: \tSecurityContext *SandboxSecurityContext `json:\"securityContext,omitempty\"`\n145: }\n146: \n147: // SandboxContainerPort defines a network port in a container.\n148: type SandboxContainerPort struct {\n149: \t// Name is the name of the port.\n150: \t// +optional\n151: \tName string `json:\"name,omitempty\"`\n152: \n153: \t// ContainerPort is the port number on the container.\n154: \t// +required\n155: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Minimum=1\n156: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Maximum=65535\n157: \tContainerPort int32 `json:\"containerPort\"`\n158: \n159: \t// Protocol is the protocol for the port.\n160: \t// +optional\n161: \t// +kubebuilder:default=TCP\n162: \tProtocol string `json:\"protocol,omitempty\"`\n163: \n164: \t// HostPort is the port number on the host.\n165: \t// +optional\n166: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Minimum=1\n167: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Maximum=65535\n168: \tHostPort int32 `json:\"hostPort,omitempty\"`\n169: }\n170: \n171: // SandboxEnvVar defines an environment variable.\n172: type SandboxEnvVar struct {\n173: \t// Name is the name of the environment variable.\n174: \t// +required\n175: \tName string `json:\"name\"`\n176: \n177: \t// Value is the literal value of the environment variable.\n178: \t// +optional\n179: \tValue string `json:\"value,omitempty\"`\n180: \n181: \t// ValueFrom specifies a source for the value.\n182: \t// +optional\n183: \tValueFrom *SandboxEnvVarSource `json:\"valueFrom,omitempty\"`\n184: }\n185: \n186: // SandboxEnvVarSource defines a source for environment variable values.\n187: type SandboxEnvVarSource struct {\n188: \t// FieldRef selects a field from the pod.\n189: \t// +optional\n190: \tFieldRef *SandboxFieldRef `json:\"fieldRef,omitempty\"`\n191: \n192: \t// ConfigMapKeyRef selects a key from a ConfigMap.\n193: \t// +optional\n194: \tConfigMapKeyRef *SandboxConfigMapKeyRef `json:\"configMapKeyRef,omitempty\"`\n195: \n196: \t// SecretKeyRef selects a key from a Secret.\n197: \t// +optional\n198: \tSecretKeyRef *SandboxSecretKeyRef `json:\"secretKeyRef,omitempty\"`\n199: }\n200: \n201: // SandboxFieldRef selects a field from a pod.\n202: type SandboxFieldRef struct {\n203: \t// FieldPath is the path of the field.\n204: \t// +required\n205: \tFieldPath string `json:\"fieldPath\"`\n206: }\n207: \n208: // SandboxConfigMapKeyRef selects a key from a ConfigMap.\n209: type SandboxConfigMapKeyRef struct {\n210: \t// Name is the name of the ConfigMap.\n211: \t// +required\n212: \tName string `json:\"name\"`\n213: \n214: \t// Key is the key to select.\n215: \t// +required\n216: \tKey string `json:\"key\"`\n217: \n218: \t// Optional specifies whether the ConfigMap must exist.\n219: \t// +optional\n220: \tOptional *bool `json:\"optional,omitempty\"`\n221: }\n222: \n223: // SandboxSecretKeyRef selects a key from a Secret.\n224: type SandboxSecretKeyRef struct {\n225: \t// Name is the name of the Secret.\n226: \t// +required\n227: \tName string `json:\"name\"`\n228: \n229: \t// Key is the key to select.\n230: \t// +required\n231: \tKey string `json:\"key\"`\n232: \n233: \t// Optional specifies whether the Secret must exist.\n234: \t// +optional\n235: \tOptional *bool `json:\"optional,omitempty\"`\n236: }\n237: \n238: // SandboxContainerResources defines resource requirements for a container.\n239: type SandboxContainerResources struct {\n240: \t// Limits defines the resource limits.\n241: \t// +optional\n242: \tLimits SandboxResourceList `json:\"limits,omitempty\"`\n243: \n244: \t// Requests defines the resource requests.\n245: \t// +optional\n246: \tRequests SandboxResourceList `json:\"requests,omitempty\"`\n247: }\n248: \n249: // SandboxResourceList defines a list of resources.\n250: type SandboxResourceList struct {\n251: \t// CPU defines CPU resources.\n252: \t// +optional\n253: \tCPU string `json:\"cpu,omitempty\"`\n254: \n255: \t// Memory defines memory resources.\n256: \t// +optional\n257: \tMemory string `json:\"memory,omitempty\"`\n258: \n259: \t// EphemeralStorage defines ephemeral storage resources.\n260: \t// +optional\n261: \tEphemeralStorage string `json:\"ephemeralStorage,omitempty\"`\n262: }\n263: \n264: // SandboxResources defines resource requirements for the pod.\n265: type SandboxResources struct {\n266: \t// Limits defines the resource limits.\n267: \t// +optional\n268: \tLimits SandboxResourceList `json:\"limits,omitempty\"`\n269: \n270: \t// Requests defines the resource requests.\n271: \t// +optional\n272: \tRequests SandboxResourceList `json:\"requests,omitempty\"`\n273: }\n274: \n275: // SandboxVolumeMount defines a volume mount.\n276: type SandboxVolumeMount struct {\n277: \t// Name is the name of the volume.\n278: \t// +required\n279: \tName string `json:\"name\"`\n280: \n281: \t// MountPath is the path within the container.\n282: \t// +required\n283: \tMountPath string `json:\"mountPath\"`\n284: \n285: \t// SubPath is the sub-path within the volume.\n286: \t// +optional\n287: \tSubPath string `json:\"subPath,omitempty\"`\n288: \n289: \t// ReadOnly specifies whether the volume is read-only.\n290: \t// +optional\n291: \tReadOnly bool `json:\"readOnly,omitempty\"`\n292: }\n293: \n294: // SandboxVolume defines a volume.\n295: type SandboxVolume struct {\n296: \t// Name is the name of the volume.\n297: \t// +required\n298: \tName string `json:\"name\"`\n299: \n300: \t// EmptyDir defines an empty directory volume.\n301: \t// +optional\n302: \tEmptyDir *SandboxEmptyDirVolumeSource `json:\"emptyDir,omitempty\"`\n303: \n304: \t// ConfigMap defines a ConfigMap volume.\n305: \t// +optional\n306: \tConfigMap *SandboxConfigMapVolumeSource `json:\"configMap,omitempty\"`\n307: \n308: \t// Secret defines a Secret volume.\n309: \t// +optional\n310: \tSecret *SandboxSecretVolumeSource `json:\"secret,omitempty\"`\n311: \n312: \t// PersistentVolumeClaim defines a PVC volume.\n313: \t// +optional\n314: \tPersistentVolumeClaim *SandboxPersistentVolumeClaimVolumeSource `json:\"persistentVolumeClaim,omitempty\"`\n315: }\n316: \n317: // SandboxEmptyDirVolumeSource defines an empty directory volume.\n318: type SandboxEmptyDirVolumeSource struct {\n319: \t// SizeLimit is the limit on the size of the volume.\n320: \t// +optional\n321: \tSizeLimit string `json:\"sizeLimit,omitempty\"`\n322: }\n323: \n324: // SandboxConfigMapVolumeSource defines a ConfigMap volume.\n325: type SandboxConfigMapVolumeSource struct {\n326: \t// Name is the name of the ConfigMap.\n327: \t// +required\n328: \tName string `json:\"name\"`\n329: \n330: \t// Optional specifies whether the ConfigMap must exist.\n331: \t// +optional\n332: \tOptional *bool `json:\"optional,omitempty\"`\n333: \n334: \t// Items specifies keys to use and the path to mount them at.\n335: \t// +optional\n336: \tItems []SandboxKeyToPath `json:\"items,omitempty\"`\n337: }\n338: \n339: // SandboxSecretVolumeSource defines a Secret volume.\n340: type SandboxSecretVolumeSource struct {\n341: \t// SecretName is the name of the Secret.\n342: \t// +required\n343: \tSecretName string `json:\"secretName\"`\n344: \n345: \t// Optional specifies whether the Secret must exist.\n346: \t// +optional\n347: \tOptional *bool `json:\"optional,omitempty\"`\n348: \n349: \t// Items specifies keys to use and the path to mount them at.\n350: \t// +optional\n351: \tItems []SandboxKeyToPath `json:\"items,omitempty\"`\n352: }\n353: \n354: // SandboxPersistentVolumeClaimVolumeSource defines a PVC volume.\n355: type SandboxPersistentVolumeClaimVolumeSource struct {\n356: \t// ClaimName is the name of the PVC.\n357: \t// +required\n358: \tClaimName string `json:\"claimName\"`\n359: \n360: \t// ReadOnly specifies whether the volume is read-only.\n361: \t// +optional\n362: \tReadOnly bool `json:\"readOnly,omitempty\"`\n363: }\n364: \n365: // SandboxKeyToPath maps a key to a path.\n366: type SandboxKeyToPath struct {\n367: \t// Key is the key to reference.\n368: \t// +required\n369: \tKey string `json:\"key\"`\n370: \n371: \t// Path is the relative path within the mount point.\n372: \t// +required\n373: \tPath string `json:\"path\"`\n374: \n375: \t// Mode is the octal permission bits.\n376: \t// +optional\n377: \tMode *int32 `json:\"mode,omitempty\"`\n378: }\n379: \n380: // SandboxProbe defines a probe.\n381: type SandboxProbe struct {\n382: \t// ProbeHandler defines the probe handler.\n383: \tSandboxProbeHandler `json:\",inline\"`\n384: \n385: \t// InitialDelaySeconds is the delay before the first probe.\n386: \t// +optional\n387: \t// +kubebuilder:default=0\n388: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Minimum=0\n389: \tInitialDelaySeconds int32 `json:\"initialDelaySeconds,omitempty\"`\n390: \n391: \t// TimeoutSeconds is the timeout for the probe.\n392: \t// +optional\n393: \t// +kubebuilder:default=1\n394: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Minimum=1\n395: \tTimeoutSeconds int32 `json:\"timeoutSeconds,omitempty\"`\n396: \n397: \t// PeriodSeconds is the period between probes.\n398: \t// +optional\n399: \t// +kubebuilder:default=10\n400: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Minimum=1\n401: \tPeriodSeconds int32 `json:\"periodSeconds,omitempty\"`\n402: \n403: \t// SuccessThreshold is the number of successes to consider successful.\n404: \t// +optional\n405: \t// +kubebuilder:default=1\n406: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Minimum=1\n407: \tSuccessThreshold int32 `json:\"successThreshold,omitempty\"`\n408: \n409: \t// FailureThreshold is the number of failures to consider failed.\n410: \t// +optional\n411: \t// +kubebuilder:default=3\n412: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Minimum=1\n413: \tFailureThreshold int32 `json:\"failureThreshold,omitempty\"`\n414: }\n415: \n416: // SandboxProbeHandler defines the probe handler.\n417: type SandboxProbeHandler struct {\n418: \t// ExecAction specifies an action to execute in the container.\n419: \t// +optional\n420: \tExec *SandboxExecAction `json:\"exec,omitempty\"`\n421: \n422: \t// TCPSocketAction specifies a TCP socket check.\n423: \t// +optional\n424: \tTCPSocket *SandboxTCPSocketAction `json:\"tcpSocket,omitempty\"`\n425: \n426: \t// HTTPGetAction specifies an HTTP GET check.\n427: \t// +optional\n428: \tHTTPGet *SandboxHTTPGetAction `json:\"httpGet,omitempty\"`\n429: }\n430: \n431: // SandboxExecAction defines an exec action.\n432: type SandboxExecAction struct {\n433: \t// Command is the command to execute.\n434: \t// +required\n435: \tCommand []string `json:\"command\"`\n436: }\n437: \n438: // SandboxTCPSocketAction defines a TCP socket check.\n439: type SandboxTCPSocketAction struct {\n440: \t// Port is the port number or name.\n441: \t// +required\n442: \tPort intstr.IntOrString `json:\"port\"`\n443: \n444: \t// Host is the host to connect to.\n445: \t// +optional\n446: \tHost string `json:\"host,omitempty\"`\n447: }\n448: \n449: // SandboxHTTPGetAction defines an HTTP GET check.\n450: type SandboxHTTPGetAction struct {\n451: \t// Port is the port number or name.\n452: \t// +required\n453: \tPort intstr.IntOrString `json:\"port\"`\n454: \n455: \t// Host is the host to connect to.\n456: \t// +optional\n457: \tHost string `json:\"host,omitempty\"`\n458: \n459: \t// Path is the path to request.\n460: \t// +optional\n461: \tPath string `json:\"path,omitempty\"`\n462: \n463: \t// Scheme is the URI scheme.\n464: \t// +optional\n465: \t// +kubebuilder:default=HTTP\n466: \tScheme string `json:\"scheme,omitempty\"`\n467: \n468: \t// HTTPHeaders specifies custom headers.\n469: \t// +optional\n470: \tHTTPHeaders []SandboxHTTPHeader `json:\"httpHeaders,omitempty\"`\n471: }\n472: \n473: // SandboxHTTPHeader defines an HTTP header.\n474: type SandboxHTTPHeader struct {\n475: \t// Name is the header name.\n476: \t// +required\n477: \tName string `json:\"name\"`\n478: \n479: \t// Value is the header value.\n480: \t// +required\n481: \tValue string `json:\"value\"`\n482: }\n483: \n484: // SandboxSecurityContext defines security settings.\n485: type SandboxSecurityContext struct {\n486: \t// RunAsUser is the UID to run the entrypoint of the container.\n487: \t// +optional\n488: \tRunAsUser *int64 `json:\"runAsUser,omitempty\"`\n489: \n490: \t// RunAsGroup is the GID to run the entrypoint of the container.\n491: \t// +optional\n492: \tRunAsGroup *int64 `json:\"runAsGroup,omitempty\"`\n493: \n494: \t// RunAsNonRoot specifies whether the container must run as non-root.\n495: \t// +optional\n496: \tRunAsNonRoot *bool `json:\"runAsNonRoot,omitempty\"`\n497: \n498: \t// ReadOnlyRootFilesystem specifies whether the root filesystem is read-only.\n499: \t// +optional\n500: \tReadOnlyRootFilesystem *bool `json:\"readOnlyRootFilesystem,omitempty\"`\n501: \n502: \t// AllowPrivilegeEscalation specifies whether a process can gain privileges.\n503: \t// +optional\n504: \tAllowPrivilegeEscalation *bool `json:\"allowPrivilegeEscalation,omitempty\"`\n505: \n506: \t// Capabilities defines Linux capabilities.\n507: \t// +optional\n508: \tCapabilities *SandboxCapabilities `json:\"capabilities,omitempty\"`\n509: \n510: \t// SeccompProfile defines the seccomp profile.\n511: \t// +optional\n512: \tSeccompProfile *SandboxSeccompProfile `json:\"seccompProfile,omitempty\"`\n513: \n514: \t// Privileged specifies whether to run in privileged mode.\n515: \t// +optional\n516: \tPrivileged *bool `json:\"privileged,omitempty\"`\n517: \n518: \t// ProcMount specifies the proc mount type.\n519: \t// +optional\n520: \tProcMount string `json:\"procMount,omitempty\"`\n521: }\n522: \n523: // SandboxCapabilities defines Linux capabilities.\n524: type SandboxCapabilities struct {\n525: \t// Add is the list of capabilities to add.\n526: \t// +optional\n527: \tAdd []string `json:\"add,omitempty\"`\n528: \n529: \t// Drop is the list of capabilities to drop.\n530: \t// +optional\n531: \tDrop []string `json:\"drop,omitempty\"`\n532: }\n533: \n534: // SandboxSeccompProfile defines the seccomp profile.\n535: type SandboxSeccompProfile struct {\n536: \t// Type is the type of seccomp profile.\n537: \t// +required\n538: \tType string `json:\"type\"`\n539: \n540: \t// LocalhostProfile references a local profile.\n541: \t// +optional\n542: \tLocalhostProfile string `json:\"localhostProfile,omitempty\"`\n543: }\n544: \n545: // SandboxAffinity defines pod scheduling constraints.\n546: type SandboxAffinity struct {\n547: \t// NodeAffinity defines node affinity.\n548: \t// +optional\n549: \tNodeAffinity *SandboxNodeAffinity `json:\"nodeAffinity,omitempty\"`\n550: \n551: \t// PodAffinity defines pod affinity.\n552: \t// +optional\n553: \tPodAffinity *SandboxPodAffinity `json:\"podAffinity,omitempty\"`\n554: \n555: \t// PodAntiAffinity defines pod anti-affinity.\n556: \t// +optional\n557: \tPodAntiAffinity *SandboxPodAffinity `json:\"podAntiAffinity,omitempty\"`\n558: }\n559: \n560: // SandboxNodeAffinity defines node affinity.\n561: type SandboxNodeAffinity struct {\n562: \t// RequiredDuringSchedulingIgnoredDuringExecution defines required node selectors.\n563: \t// +optional\n564: \tRequiredDuringSchedulingIgnoredDuringExecution *SandboxNodeSelector `json:\"requiredDuringSchedulingIgnoredDuringExecution,omitempty\"`\n565: \n566: \t// PreferredDuringSchedulingIgnoredDuringExecution defines preferred node selectors.\n567: \t// +optional\n568: \tPreferredDuringSchedulingIgnoredDuringExecution []SandboxPreferredSchedulingTerm `json:\"preferredDuringSchedulingIgnoredDuringExecution,omitempty\"`\n569: }\n570: \n571: // SandboxNodeSelector defines a node selector.\n572: type SandboxNodeSelector struct {\n573: \t// NodeSelectorTerms is the list of node selector terms.\n574: \t// +required\n575: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:MinItems=1\n576: \tNodeSelectorTerms []SandboxNodeSelectorTerm `json:\"nodeSelectorTerms\"`\n577: }\n578: \n579: // SandboxNodeSelectorTerm defines a node selector term.\n580: type SandboxNodeSelectorTerm struct {\n581: \t// MatchExpressions is a list of node selector requirements.\n582: \t// +optional\n583: \tMatchExpressions []SandboxNodeSelectorRequirement `json:\"matchExpressions,omitempty\"`\n584: \n585: \t// MatchFields is a list of node selector field requirements.\n586: \t// +optional\n587: \tMatchFields []SandboxNodeSelectorRequirement `json:\"matchFields,omitempty\"`\n588: }\n589: \n590: // SandboxNodeSelectorRequirement defines a node selector requirement.\n591: type SandboxNodeSelectorRequirement struct {\n592: \t// Key is the label key.\n593: \t// +required\n594: \tKey string `json:\"key\"`\n595: \n596: \t// Operator is the operator.\n597: \t// +required\n598: \tOperator string `json:\"operator\"`\n599: \n600: \t// Values is the values.\n601: \t// +optional\n602: \tValues []string `json:\"values,omitempty\"`\n603: }\n604: \n605: // SandboxPreferredSchedulingTerm defines a preferred scheduling term.\n606: type SandboxPreferredSchedulingTerm struct {\n607: \t// Weight is the weight.\n608: \t// +required\n609: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Minimum=1\n610: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Maximum=100\n611: \tWeight int32 `json:\"weight\"`\n612: \n613: \t// Preference is the preference.\n614: \t// +required\n615: \tPreference SandboxNodeSelectorTerm `json:\"preference\"`\n616: }\n617: \n618: // SandboxPodAffinity defines pod affinity.\n619: type SandboxPodAffinity struct {\n620: \t// RequiredDuringSchedulingIgnoredDuringExecution defines required pod selectors.\n621: \t// +optional\n622: \tRequiredDuringSchedulingIgnoredDuringExecution []SandboxPodAffinityTerm `json:\"requiredDuringSchedulingIgnoredDuringExecution,omitempty\"`\n623: \n624: \t// PreferredDuringSchedulingIgnoredDuringExecution defines preferred pod selectors.\n625: \t// +optional\n626: \tPreferredDuringSchedulingIgnoredDuringExecution []SandboxWeightedPodAffinityTerm `json:\"preferredDuringSchedulingIgnoredDuringExecution,omitempty\"`\n627: }\n628: \n629: // SandboxPodAffinityTerm defines a pod affinity term.\n630: type SandboxPodAffinityTerm struct {\n631: \t// LabelSelector defines the label selector.\n632: \t// +optional\n633: \tLabelSelector *SandboxLabelSelector `json:\"labelSelector,omitempty\"`\n634: \n635: \t// Namespaces specifies the namespaces.\n636: \t// +optional\n637: \tNamespaces []string `json:\"namespaces,omitempty\"`\n638: \n639: \t// TopologyKey is the topology key.\n640: \t// +required\n641: \tTopologyKey string `json:\"topologyKey\"`\n642: \n643: \t// NamespaceSelector defines the namespace selector.\n644: \t// +optional\n645: \tNamespaceSelector *SandboxLabelSelector `json:\"namespaceSelector,omitempty\"`\n646: }\n647: \n648: // SandboxLabelSelector defines a label selector.\n649: type SandboxLabelSelector struct {\n650: \t// MatchLabels is a map of label keys and values.\n651: \t// +optional\n652: \tMatchLabels map[string]string `json:\"matchLabels,omitempty\"`\n653: \n654: \t// MatchExpressions is a list of label selector requirements.\n655: \t// +optional\n656: \tMatchExpressions []SandboxLabelSelectorRequirement `json:\"matchExpressions,omitempty\"`\n657: }\n658: \n659: // SandboxLabelSelectorRequirement defines a label selector requirement.\n660: type SandboxLabelSelectorRequirement struct {\n661: \t// Key is the label key.\n662: \t// +required\n663: \tKey string `json:\"key\"`\n664: \n665: \t// Operator is the operator.\n666: \t// +required\n667: \tOperator string `json:\"operator\"`\n668: \n669: \t// Values is the values.\n670: \t// +optional\n671: \tValues []string `json:\"values,omitempty\"`\n672: }\n673: \n674: // SandboxWeightedPodAffinityTerm defines a weighted pod affinity term.\n675: type SandboxWeightedPodAffinityTerm struct {\n676: \t// Weight is the weight.\n677: \t// +required\n678: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Minimum=1\n679: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Maximum=100\n680: \tWeight int32 `json:\"weight\"`\n681: \n682: \t// PodAffinityTerm is the pod affinity term.\n683: \t// +required\n684: \tPodAffinityTerm SandboxPodAffinityTerm `json:\"podAffinityTerm\"`\n685: }\n686: \n687: // SandboxToleration defines a pod toleration.\n688: type SandboxToleration struct {\n689: \t// Key is the toleration key.\n690: \t// +optional\n691: \tKey string `json:\"key,omitempty\"`\n692: \n693: \t// Operator is the toleration operator.\n694: \t// +optional\n695: \tOperator string `json:\"operator,omitempty\"`\n696: \n697: \t// Value is the toleration value.\n698: \t// +optional\n699: \tValue string `json:\"value,omitempty\"`\n700: \n701: \t// Effect is the toleration effect.\n702: \t// +optional\n703: \tEffect string `json:\"effect,omitempty\"`\n704: \n705: \t// TolerationSeconds is the toleration duration.\n706: \t// +optional\n707: \tTolerationSeconds *int64 `json:\"tolerationSeconds,omitempty\"`\n708: }\n709: \n710: // AgentRuntimeStatus defines the observed state of an AgentRuntime.\n711: type AgentRuntimeStatus struct {\n712: \t// Conditions represent the latest available observations of the AgentRuntime's current state.\n713: \t// +optional\n714: \tConditions []metav1.Condition `json:\"conditions,omitempty\"`\n715: \n716: \t// ObservedGeneration is the most recent generation observed by the controller.\n717: \t// +optional\n718: \tObservedGeneration int64 `json:\"observedGeneration,omitempty\"`\n719: }\n720: \n721: // +k8s:deepcopy-gen:interfaces=k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object\n722: \n723: // AgentRuntimeList contains a list of AgentRuntime objects.\n724: type AgentRuntimeList struct {\n725: \tmetav1.TypeMeta `json:\",inline\"`\n726: \tmetav1.ListMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n727: \n728: \tItems []AgentRuntime `json:\"items\"`\n729: }\n730: \n731: // +genclient\n732: // +k8s:deepcopy-gen:interfaces=k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object\n733: // +k8s:openapi-gen=true\n734: // +kubebuilder:resource:shortName=ci;codeinterpreter\n735: // +kubebuilder:subresource:status\n736: // +kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"Ready\",type=\"boolean\",JSONPath=\".status.ready\"\n737: // +kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"Runtime\",type=\"string\",JSONPath=\".spec.runtime\"\n738: // +kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"Age\",type=\"date\",JSONPath=\".metadata.creationTimestamp\"\n739: \n740: // CodeInterpreter defines a custom resource for managing code execution environments.\n741: // It represents a code interpreter sandbox that executes user code in a secure environment.\n742: type CodeInterpreter struct {\n743: \tmetav1.TypeMeta   `json:\",inline\"`\n744: \tmetav1.ObjectMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n745: \n746: \tSpec   CodeInterpreterSpec   `json:\"spec,omitempty\"`\n747: \tStatus CodeInterpreterStatus `json:\"status,omitempty\"`\n748: }\n749: \n750: // CodeInterpreterSpec defines the desired state of a CodeInterpreter.\n751: type CodeInterpreterSpec struct {\n752: \t// Image is the container image for the interpreter (e.g., \"python:3.11-slim\").\n753: \t// +required\n754: \tImage string `json:\"image\"`\n755: \n756: \t// Runtime specifies the execution environment type.\n757: \t// +kubebuilder:default=\"python\"\n758: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Enum=python;javascript;typescript;go\n759: \t// +optional\n760: \tRuntime string `json:\"runtime,omitempty\"`\n761: \n762: \t// Timeout defines the maximum execution time for code snippets.\n763: \t// +kubebuilder:default=\"5m\"\n764: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Type=string\n765: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Format=duration\n766: \t// +optional\n767: \tTimeout *metav1.Duration `json:\"timeout,omitempty\"`\n768: \n769: \t// Resources defines compute resource requirements for the interpreter container.\n770: \t// +optional\n771: \tResources *SandboxContainerResources `json:\"resources,omitempty\"`\n772: \n773: \t// Env defines environment variables to inject into the interpreter container.\n774: \t// +optional\n775: \tEnv []SandboxEnvVar `json:\"env,omitempty\"`\n776: \n777: \t// EnabledPackages specifies allowed packages for the interpreter.\n778: \t// Only packages listed here can be imported/required. Empty list allows all.\n779: \t// +optional\n780: \tEnabledPackages []string `json:\"enabledPackages,omitempty\"`\n781: }\n782: \n783: // CodeInterpreterStatus defines the observed state of a CodeInterpreter.\n784: type CodeInterpreterStatus struct {\n785: \t// Ready indicates whether the interpreter is ready to execute code.\n786: \t// +optional\n787: \tReady bool `json:\"ready,omitempty\"`\n788: \n789: \t// Conditions represent the latest available observations of the CodeInterpreter's current state.\n790: \t// +optional\n791: \tConditions []metav1.Condition `json:\"conditions,omitempty\"`\n792: \n793: \t// ObservedGeneration is the most recent generation observed by the controller.\n794: \t// +optional\n795: \tObservedGeneration int64 `json:\"observedGeneration,omitempty\"`\n796: }\n797: \n798: // +k8s:deepcopy-gen:interfaces=k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object\n799: \n800: // CodeInterpreterList contains a list of CodeInterpreter objects.\n801: type CodeInterpreterList struct {\n802: \tmetav1.TypeMeta `json:\",inline\"`\n803: \tmetav1.ListMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n804: \n805: \tItems []CodeInterpreter `json:\"items\"`\n806: }\n\n(End of file - total 806 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"package v1alpha1\n\nimport (\n\tmetav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n\t\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/util/intstr\"\n)\n\n// +genclient\n// +genclient:nonNamespaced\n// +k8s:deepcopy-gen:interfaces=k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object\n// +k8s:openapi-gen=true\n// +kubebuilder:resource:shortName=ar;agentruntime\n// +kubebuilder:subresource:status\n// +kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"Age\",type=\"date\",JSONPath=\".metadata.creationTimestamp\"\n\n// AgentRuntime defines a custom resource for managing agent runtime configurations.\n// It represents a sandbox orchestration runtime that manages the lifecycle of agent pods.\ntype AgentRuntime struct {\n\tmetav1.TypeMeta   `json:\",inline\"`\n\tmetav1.ObjectMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go","time":{"start":1775841005808,"end":1775841005844}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775841005849,"sessionID":"ses_287a0d953ffeprum1kjA3lYblB","part":{"id":"prt_d785f4ec8001C9qpZcxyNsaZz9","messageID":"msg_d785f456a001G5HWGctPntsdO1","sessionID":"ses_287a0d953ffeprum1kjA3lYblB","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-cd0dd65f2d3b4cf2a4961cff241e96e2","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/README.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/README.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube Runtime API\n2: \n3: This package contains the Kubernetes API definitions for the AgentCube runtime resources.\n4: \n5: ## API Group\n6: \n7: - **Group**: `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`\n8: - **Version**: `v1alpha1`\n9: - **Kinds**: `AgentRuntime`, `CodeInterpreter`\n10: \n11: ## Types\n12: \n13: ### AgentRuntime\n14: \n15: `AgentRuntime` is a Kubernetes custom resource that defines a sandbox orchestration runtime for managing the lifecycle of agent pods.\n16: \n17: #### Spec\n18: \n19: The `AgentRuntimeSpec` defines the desired state of an AgentRuntime:\n20: \n21: - **PodTemplate** (*SandboxTemplate, required): Template for creating sandbox pods\n22: - **SessionTimeout** (*metav1.Duration, optional): Timeout for idle sessions before cleanup (default: 15m)\n23: - **MaxSessionDuration** (*metav1.Duration, optional): Maximum allowed duration for a session (default: 8h)\n24: \n25: #### Status\n26: \n27: The `AgentRuntimeStatus` defines the observed state of an AgentRuntime:\n28: \n29: - **Conditions** ([]metav1.Condition, optional): List of conditions representing the runtime state\n30: - **ObservedGeneration** (int64, optional): Most recent generation observed by the controller\n31: \n32: ### CodeInterpreter\n33: \n34: `CodeInterpreter` is a Kubernetes custom resource that defines a code execution environment for managing interpreter sandboxes.\n35: \n36: #### Spec\n37: \n38: The `CodeInterpreterSpec` defines the desired state of a CodeInterpreter:\n39: \n40: - **Image** (string, required): Container image for the interpreter (e.g., \"python:3.11-slim\")\n41: - **Runtime** (string, optional): Execution environment type (default: \"python\")\n42:   - Allowed values: `python`, `javascript`, `typescript`, `go`\n43: - **Timeout** (*metav1.Duration, optional): Maximum execution time for code snippets (default: 5m)\n44: - **Resources** (*SandboxContainerResources, optional): Compute resource requirements\n45: - **Env** ([]SandboxEnvVar, optional): Environment variables to inject\n46: - **EnabledPackages** ([]string, optional): Allowed packages for the interpreter\n47: \n48: #### Status\n49: \n50: The `CodeInterpreterStatus` defines the observed state of a CodeInterpreter:\n51: \n52: - **Ready** (bool, optional): Whether the interpreter is ready to execute code\n53: - **Conditions** ([]metav1.Condition, optional): List of conditions representing the interpreter state\n54: - **ObservedGeneration** (int64, optional): Most recent generation observed by the controller\n55: \n56: ### SandboxTemplate\n57: \n58: Defines the template for creating sandbox pods:\n59: \n60: - **Metadata** (*SandboxMetadata, optional): Labels and annotations for the pod\n61: - **Spec** (SandboxPodSpec, required): Pod specification\n62: \n63: ### SandboxPodSpec\n64: \n65: Defines the pod specification for sandbox pods:\n66: \n67: - **Containers** ([]SandboxContainer, required): List of containers in the pod\n68: - **NodeSelector** (map[string]string, optional): Node selection constraints\n69: - **Affinity** (*SandboxAffinity, optional): Pod scheduling constraints\n70: - **Tolerations** ([]SandboxToleration, optional): Pod tolerations\n71: - **ResourceRequirements** (*SandboxResources, optional): Resource requirements for the pod\n72: - **Volumes** ([]SandboxVolume, optional): Pod volumes\n73: \n74: ## Usage\n75: \n76: ### Creating an AgentRuntime\n77: \n78: ```yaml\n79: apiVersion: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1\n80: kind: AgentRuntime\n81: metadata:\n82:   name: example-runtime\n83:   namespace: default\n84: spec:\n85:   podTemplate:\n86:     spec:\n87:       containers:\n88:       - name: agent\n89:         image: agent:latest\n90:         ports:\n91:         - containerPort: 8080\n92: ```\n93: \n94: ### Creating a CodeInterpreter\n95: \n96: ```yaml\n97: apiVersion: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1\n98: kind: CodeInterpreter\n99: metadata:\n100:   name: python-interpreter\n101:   namespace: default\n102: spec:\n103:   image: python:3.11-slim\n104:   runtime: python\n105:   timeout: 5m\n106:   resources:\n107:     limits:\n108:       cpu: \"1\"\n109:       memory: \"1Gi\"\n110:     requests:\n111:       cpu: \"250m\"\n112:       memory: \"256Mi\"\n113:   enabledPackages:\n114:   - numpy\n115:   - pandas\n116:   env:\n117:   - name: PYTHON_VERSION\n118:     value: \"3.11\"\n119: ```\n120: \n121: ### Using with client-go\n122: \n123: #### Creating an AgentRuntime\n124: \n125: ```go\n126: import (\n127:     \"context\"\n128:     \"time\"\n129: \n130:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1\"\n131:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go/clientset/versioned\"\n132:     metav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n133: )\n134: \n135: func createAgentRuntime(clientset *versioned.Clientset) error {\n136:     runtime := &v1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n137:         ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n138:             Name:      \"example-runtime\",\n139:             Namespace: \"default\",\n140:         },\n141:         Spec: v1alpha1.AgentRuntimeSpec{\n142:             PodTemplate: &v1alpha1.SandboxTemplate{\n143:                 Spec: v1alpha1.SandboxPodSpec{\n144:                     Containers: []v1alpha1.SandboxContainer{\n145:                         {\n146:                             Name:  \"agent\",\n147:                             Image: \"agent:latest\",\n148:                         },\n149:                     },\n150:                 },\n151:             },\n152:         },\n153:     }\n154: \n155:     _, err := clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(\"default\").Create(\n156:         context.TODO(),\n157:         runtime,\n158:         metav1.CreateOptions{},\n159:     )\n160:     return err\n161: }\n162: ```\n163: \n164: #### Creating a CodeInterpreter\n165: \n166: ```go\n167: import (\n168:     \"context\"\n169:     \"time\"\n170: \n171:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1\"\n172:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go/clientset/versioned\"\n173:     metav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n174: )\n175: \n176: func createCodeInterpreter(clientset *versioned.Clientset) error {\n177:     timeout := &metav1.Duration{Duration: 5 * time.Minute}\n178: \n179:     interpreter := &v1alpha1.CodeInterpreter{\n180:         ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n181:             Name:      \"python-interpreter\",\n182:             Namespace: \"default\",\n183:         },\n184:         Spec: v1alpha1.CodeInterpreterSpec{\n185:             Image:   \"python:3.11-slim\",\n186:             Runtime: \"python\",\n187:             Timeout: timeout,\n188:             EnabledPackages: []string{\"numpy\", \"pandas\"},\n189:         },\n190:     }\n191: \n192:     _, err := clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().CodeInterpreters(\"default\").Create(\n193:         context.TODO(),\n194:         interpreter,\n195:         metav1.CreateOptions{},\n196:     )\n197:     return err\n198: }\n199: ```\n200: \n201: ## Testing\n202: \n203: Run the unit tests:\n204: \n205: ```bash\n206: go test ./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/...\n207: ```\n208: \n209: The test suite includes:\n210: - AgentRuntime type tests\n211: - CodeInterpreter type tests\n212: - Sandbox configuration tests\n213: - DeepCopy functionality tests\n214: - JSON serialization tests\n215: - Scheme registration tests\n216: \n217: ## CRD Installation\n218: \n219: The CRD YAML files are located at `config/crd/bases/`:\n220: \n221: - `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_agentruntimes.yaml`\n222: - `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_codeinterpreters.yaml`\n223: \n224: Install the CRDs:\n225: \n226: ```bash\n227: kubectl apply -f config/crd/bases/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_agentruntimes.yaml\n228: kubectl apply -f config/crd/bases/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_codeinterpreters.yaml\n229: ```\n230: \n231: Verify installation:\n232: \n233: ```bash\n234: kubectl get crd agentruntimes.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\n235: kubectl get crd codeinterpreters.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\n236: ```\n237: \n238: ## Features\n239: \n240: ### AgentRuntime\n241: \n242: - **Kubernetes-native**: Leverages Kubernetes CRD and controller patterns\n243: - **Type-safe**: Generated Go types for compile-time safety\n244: - **Extensible**: Supports custom pod templates, volumes, and configurations\n245: - **Status tracking**: Built-in conditions for runtime state management\n246: - **Resource management**: Support for resource limits, requests, and scheduling constraints\n247: - **Security**: Full support for security contexts, capabilities, and seccomp profiles\n248: \n249: ### CodeInterpreter\n250: \n251: - **Multi-language support**: Python, JavaScript, TypeScript, and Go runtimes\n252: - **Resource management**: Configurable CPU, memory, and ephemeral storage limits\n253: - **Timeout enforcement**: Maximum execution time for code snippets\n254: - **Package filtering**: Allowed packages for enhanced security\n255: - **Environment injection**: Custom environment variables support\n256: - **Status tracking**: Ready status and conditions for interpreter state\n257: \n258: ## License\n259: \n260: Copyright 2024 Volcano Authors.\n\n(End of file - total 260 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AgentCube Runtime API\n\nThis package contains the Kubernetes API definitions for the AgentCube runtime resources.\n\n## API Group\n\n- **Group**: `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`\n- **Version**: `v1alpha1`\n- **Kinds**: `AgentRuntime`, `CodeInterpreter`\n\n## Types\n\n### AgentRuntime\n\n`AgentRuntime` is a Kubernetes custom resource that defines a sandbox orchestration runtime for managing the lifecycle of agent pods.\n\n#### Spec\n\nThe `AgentRuntimeSpec` defines the desired state of an AgentRuntime:\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/README.md","time":{"start":1775841005812,"end":1775841005847}}}}
